    "details": "Ciaran McCreesh discovered news ways in which a VIM modeline\ncan be used to trojan a text file. The patch by Bram\nMoolenaar reads:\n\n> Problem: Unusual characters in an option value may cause\n> unexpected behavior, especially for a modeline. (Ciaran\n> McCreesh)\n>\n> Solution: Don't allow setting termcap options or\n> 'printdevice' or 'titleold' in a modeline. Don't list\n> options for \"termcap\" and \"all\" in a modeline. Don't allow\n> unusual characters in 'filetype', 'syntax', 'backupext',\n> 'keymap', 'patchmode' and 'langmenu'.\n\n**Note:** It is generally recommended that VIM\nusers use `set nomodeline` in\n`~/.vimrc` to avoid the possibility of trojaned\ntext files.",
    "id": "FreeBSD-kernel-2005-0319",
